Build main pipeline      Build dev pipeline
Why is this useful?

Imagine a team of 10 developers:

8 developers work on the dev branch.
1 developer fixes a production issue on the main branch.

If someone pushes to dev, Jenkins doesn't rebuild main, because there were no changes there. Only the pipeline for the changed branch runs, saving build time and resources.

Interview Answer

Q: In a Multibranch Pipeline, if a developer commits only to the dev branch, will Jenkins build all branches?

Answer: No. Jenkins creates a separate pipeline for each discovered branch. When a commit is pushed to dev, only the dev branch pipeline is triggered. The main branch pipeline is not
triggered unless there is a change in the main branch (or someone manually starts a build). This allows each branch to be built and tested independently.
